            <h4><p>-First of all, the most important thing you have to know about this aplication, is, what is this?</p></h4>
            <h5>This is a Web Application, and if you put a GitHub URL on the top, it retrieves information about its forks and currently calculates the Pylint rating for each one of the forks. The result is a list of the nine best forks of the repository sorted by this rating.</h5>
            <br>
            <h4><p>-How does it work?</p></h4>
            <h5>You only have to put the URL of the repository you are interested in, and also your email. We ask for an email,mainly because in case of a big repository, it could take several minutes, and if you add your email, we will contact with you as soon as it will be able. Then, you can see the results of the analysis</h5>   
            <br>
            <h4><p>-How many programming languages support?</p></h4>
            <h5>Actually, it's support only one language, only Python.</h5>  
            <br>  
            <h4><p>-And if there is an error that I dont want to have in consideration?</p></h4>
            <h5>Don't worry! We have put some filters, not to considered it. You can see that filters on the righ. Or on the bottom if you are surfing with a mobile phone or tablet.</h5>
            <br>
            <h4><p>-How many time BestFork save my results?</p></h4>
            <h5>We dont know that information, it depends on our servers, nevertheless you can calculate it again.</h5>  
            <br>   
            <h4><p>-How I could see the errors?</p></h4>
            <h5>If you want to see the errors, you only have to do click, on the repository name.</h5> 
            <br>      
            <h4><p>-BestFork doesn't show me nothing?</p></h4>
            <h5> 1st. Check if really there are something in that repository</h5>
            <h5> 2nd. This Aplication, only works with python, check if there are python files in that repository</h5>  
            <h5> 3rd. If the repository have many and big errors, it can have a negative score</h5>
            <h5> 4th. If the problem persists contact us</h5>  
            <br>
            <h4><p>-BestFork doesn't show me nothing?</p></h4>
            <h5> 1st. Check if really there are something in that repository</h5>
            <br>
            <h4><p>-How many money I have to pay?</p></h4>
            <h5>It's free! You don't have to pay anything.</h5>  
